text: Lagenophora huegelii is a plant in the daisy family (Asteraceae) which is endemic to Australia and found in the states of Western Australia, South Australia, Tasmania and Victoria. It was first described in 1837 by George Bentham from specimens described as being collected by Baron Carl von Hügel and coming from the Swan River and King Georges Sound. ==References== == External links == * Lagenophora huegelii Occurrence data from the Australasian Virtual Herbarium huegelii Category:Flora of South Australia Category:Flora of Tasmania Category:Taxa named by George Bentham Category:Flora of Victoria (Australia) Category:Plants described in 1837
title: Lagenophora huegelii
